group(25.10)                                                      group(25.10)

Name
       group  -  Creates  a new module and hinst from a group of the specified
       hinsts or insts

Syntax
       group

       [-help]

       <inst>|<hInst>+

       [[-module_name <module_name> -hinst_base_name <hinst_base_name> ]]

       Creates a new module and hinst from a group of the specified hinsts  or
       insts.  You can only group hinsts and insts that belong to the same hi-
       erarchy (the same hinst parent). Returns the newly created hinst.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each group.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man group

       <inst>|<hInst>+
              Specifies  the hinst(s) or inst(s), in the same hierarchy, to be
              grouped.

       -hinst_base_name <hinst_base_name>
              Specifies the hinst base name of the new group instantiation.

       -module_name <module_name>
              Specifies the module name of the new group.

Example
       The following command groups two hinsts, h1 and h2,  at  the  top-level
       into a new module named test.The new hinst is named testi by default.

       >group       -module_name      test      -hinst_base_name      baseName
       {DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST DTMF_INST/RESULTS_CONV_INST}

